Set specific goals for each study session to stay focused.
Take regular breaks using the Pomodoro technique (25 minutes study, 5 minutes break).
Use active recall by testing yourself on the material you've studied.
Create a study schedule and stick to it consistently.
Teach what you've learned to someone else to reinforce your understanding.
Organize your study space to reduce distractions and improve concentration.
Use visual aids like mind maps and diagrams to better understand complex topics.
Practice past exams or quizzes to prepare for test-like conditions.
Limit multitasking to increase focus on a single subject or topic at a time.
Stay hydrated and get enough sleep to maintain peak cognitive function.
